<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBDFFE76DC2FB00FD17AFD3" pageId="25" pageNumber="1538" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBDFFE76DC2FB00FD17AFD3" blockId="25.[178,1085,1181,1233]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1538">
Etymology: The trivial name 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBDFFE76F45FB00FDE3AFB0" box="[565,630,1181,1202]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1538">plauta</emphasis>
is a Greek adjective derived from 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBDFFE76E92FB00FB8BAFB0" box="[994,1054,1181,1202]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1538">platys</emphasis>
(= flat). I refer to the body form of these beetles.
</paragraph>
